The paper discusses an interface for interactive visual exploration of a database, specifically the ArticleFirst database. The focus is on browsing live entities associated with articles, which involves navigating a network representation of prevailing entities such as topics, authors, journals, and Dewey decimal classes. The paper also discusses different use cases of the interface and its relevance to debates in HCI about interactive information visualization. Given this focus, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is Information Retrieval (cs.IR), followed by Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Computation and Language (cs.CL).
